
@startuml
class Student {
  -studentID: String
  -name: String
  -coursesRegistered: List<Course>
}

class TeachingAssistant {
  -taID: String
  -name: String
  -coursesTaught: List<Course>
}

class Course {
  -courseID: String
  -title: String
  -description: String
}

class Appointment {
  -appointmentID: String
  -date: Date
  -time: Time
  -duration: int
  -student: Student
  -teachingAssistant: TeachingAssistant
  -course: Course
}

Student "1" --> "0..*" Course : registered for
TeachingAssistant "1" --> "0..*" Course : teaches
Appointment "1" --> "1" Student : involves
Appointment "1" --> "1" TeachingAssistant : involves
Appointment "1" --> "1" Course : relates to

note right of Appointment
  An appointment is always for one specific course and with one particular TA.
end note

note right of Student
  A student can only request an appointment for a course they are registered for.
end note

note right of TeachingAssistant
  A TA can only provide help for courses they are teaching.
end note
@enduml

### Explanation:
- **Student** has a list of courses they're registered in.
- **TeachingAssistant** has a list of courses they are teaching.
- **Course** is a basic entity that links students and TAs.
- **Appointment** is associated with one student, one TA, and one course. It ensures that the TA is teaching the course and the student is registered for it.

